{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:galatians.5",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "galatians",
    "chapterNumber": 5,
    "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5",
    "summary": "Source text for Galatians 5 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:1",
      "text": "Stand fast and be not held again under the yoke of bondage.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:2",
      "text": "Behold, I Paul tell you, that if you be circumcised, Christ shall profit you nothing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:3",
      "text": "And I testify again to every man circumcising himself that he is a debtor to do the whole law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:4",
      "text": "You are made void of Christ, you who are justified in the law: you are fallen from grace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:5",
      "text": "For we in spirit, by faith, wait for the hope of justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:6",
      "text": "For in Christ Jesus neither circumcision availeth any thing nor uncircumcision: but faith that worketh by Charity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:7",
      "text": "You did run well. What hath hindered you, that you should not obey the truth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:8",
      "text": "This persuasion is not from him that calleth you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:9",
      "text": "A little leaven corrupteth the whole lump.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:10",
      "text": "I have confidence in you in the Lord that you will not be of another mind: but he that troubleth you shall bear the judgment, whosoever he be.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:11",
      "text": "And I, brethren, if I yet preach circumcision, why do I yet suffer persecution? Then is the scandal of the cross made void.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:12",
      "text": "I would they were even cut off, who trouble you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:13",
      "text": "For you, brethren, have been called unto liberty. Only make not liberty an occasion to the flesh: but by charity of the spirit serve one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:14",
      "text": "For all the law is fulfilled in one word: Thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:15",
      "text": "But if you bite and devour one another: take heed you be not consumed one of another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:16",
      "text": "I say then: Walk in the spirit: and you shall not fulfill the lusts of the flesh.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:17",
      "text": "For the flesh lusteth against the spirit: and the spirit against the flesh: For these are contrary one to another: so that you do not the things that you would.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:18",
      "text": "But if you are led by the spirit, you are not under the law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:19",
      "text": "Now the works of the flesh are manifest: which are fornication, uncleanness, immodesty, luxury,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:20",
      "text": "Idolatry, witchcrafts, enmities, contentions, emulations, wraths, quarrels, dissensions, sects,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:21",
      "text": "Envies, murders, drunkenness, revellings, and such like. Of the which I foretell you, as I have foretold to you, that they who do such things shall not obtain the kingdom of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:22",
      "text": "But the fruit of the Spirit is, charity, joy, peace, patience, benignity, goodness, longanimity,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:23",
      "text": "Mildness, faith, modesty, continency, chastity. Against such there is no law.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:24",
      "text": "And they that are Christ's have crucified their flesh, with the vices and concupiscences.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:25",
      "text": "If we live in the Spirit, let us also walk in the Spirit.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:galatians.5.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "galatians",
      "chapterNumber": 5,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Galatians 5:26",
      "text": "Let us not be made desirous of vain glory, provoking one another, envying one another.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
